Recipe App
This is a simple recipe app built with React and Node.js using PostgreSQL as the database.

Getting started
Prerequisites
Node.js
PostgreSQL
Installing
To install the dependencies for the server, run the following command:

npm install
To install the dependencies for the client, navigate to the client directory and run the following command:

npm install
the port opens on port 8080
Setting up the database
Create a .env file

makefile

DB_HOST=your-database-hostname
DB_PORT=your-database-port
DB_NAME=your-database-name
DB_USERNAME=your-database-username
DB_PASSWORD=your-database-password


Starting the client
To start the client, navigate to the client directory and run the following command:

sql
npm start
This will start the client on port 3000 and open a browser window displaying the app.